{
  "texts": [
    "Computational efficiency is less emphasized in SVS literature compared to speech synthesis; however, GOLF Yu and Fazekas (2023) required less than 40% GPU memory during training and provided nearly 10x faster inference speed than other DDSP SVS methods (which already supported real-time operation).",
    "This fast inference speed can facilitate downstream applications, including real-time musicking contexts or functioning in low-resource embedded devices.",
    "The task of singing voice conversion (SVC) aims to transform a recording of a source singer such that it sounds like it was sung by a given target singer.",
    "This task, related to voice conversion, introduces further challenges (Huang et al., 2023).",
    "Specifically, there are a wider range of attributes to model, such as pitch contours, singing styles, and expressive variations."
  ]
}